  "body": "Our test suite startup time is quite slow (around 8 seconds) even for running a simple test (i.e. including a single file). \r\n\r\nHere we're running 3 really simple tests and it takes 7.7 seconds:\r\n```\r\n$ time npx hardhat test --no-compile test/unit/ClaimProofs/index.js\r\n\r\n\r\n  ClaimProofs unit tests\r\n    addProof\r\n      ✓ should emit an event with coverId, ipfsHash and sender when called (212ms)\r\n      ✓ should allow anyone to submit a proof for the same coverId (67ms)\r\n      ✓ should allow someone to submit a proof multiple times (42ms)\r\n\r\n\r\n  3 passing (3s)\r\n\r\nnpx hardhat test --no-compile test/unit/ClaimProofs/index.js  14.28s user 1.26s system 200% cpu 7.734 total\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe're using hardhat with truffle5 and web3 plugins and do have a lot of artifacts (around 100) - our contracts, uniswap and various mocks. Although the number of artifacts is quite high, I think loading them shouldn't take THAT much time - I think in 2021, our laptops can handle hundreds of artifacts in under one second, so there must be some bottleneck somewhere. \r\n\r\nThe repo in this example is https://github.com/NexusMutual/smart-contracts/tree/af2d4659088f81febc9c25620d03aba375485336\r\n",
