    "body": "> If printing a help message is taking multiple seconds, it's most probably because you are using typescript, and `ts-node` recompiles everything each time you run it, and that can be slow. As a workaround, you can set the env variable `TS_NODE_TRANSPILE_ONLY=1`.\r\n> \r\n> If that doesn't help the reason is probably a plugin doing something slow during its intialization. Can you try commenting out some of them and re-running the help task?\r\n\r\nAdding `TS_NODE_TRANSPILE_ONLY=1` fixes the lag! Any chance this can get added by default or something similar to avoid the full recompile? ",
